column1: Wunder Under High-Rise Tight Engineered Full-On Luxtreme 28"
column6: I purchased "Inked Wunder Under Ice Grey Black pattern" Engineered Full-On Luxtreme in December. These were my first Luxtreme legging I purchased, so I am not sure if there are any differences between full on Luxtreme WU legging and Engineered Full-On Luxtreme, but I LOVE the fabric of these pants. Yes, it feels a little tighter than Luon, but it is not too tight. Lextreme fabric is smoother than Luon, so I think it has to be a little tighter to stay up?? I normally wear a size 6 in Luon leggings, and went with the same size in Lextreme. I tired a size 8 as well. They felt OK, but I knew they will not stay up in running. I am glad I went with my regular Luon size. I run 40-45 minutes in these, and they stay up. Love the pattern, feel, quality, and everything about the pants that I bought another Engineered Full-On Luxtreme WU in "Painted Paisley Wunder Under Silver Ice Black" in January. I LOVE both pairs.

column6: I bought these expecting a tight fit and the same quality I have gotten from the many other lulu tights I have purchased. What a huge disappointment...wore these once only. The waist band is loose, the fabric thin and see thru. I had to constantly pull these up as I worked out...and to my embarrassment, a gym-goer discreetly told me my pants were see-thru. You wont feel held-in with these tights. Wish I could return them, but I bought them from the WMTM section online.

column1: Wunder Under High-Rise Tight Engineered Full-On Luxtreme 28"
column6: I fell in love with this "Inked Wunder Under Ice Grey Black pattern" WU, and had to try them on! They felt similar to the Align pant but tighter? I went with my usual size 8 and they do fit snug, but feel great and stay in place through the whole class!! No hiking up my pants or worrying about wedgies lol. This pattern accented my curves rather than making them look bigger! ;) The only drawback for me is the short length (I'm 5'6"), but I still bought them and love them!!

column1: Wunder Under High-Rise Tight Engineered Full-On Luxtreme 28"
column6:
These were my first pair of leggings that had a design and I do not regret the decision! Not see thru, has some stretch, and makes my butt look great!
I do feel the material is a bit thinner then my other Full On Luxtreme pants but because of the print you can't notice.
Only downfall is the length but I am 5'2 and expected this (plus Lulu offers free hemming).
